definitions.definition: Ellipsis of tomato ketchup ( “ a tomato - vinegar -based sauce , sometimes containing spices , onion or garlic , and (especially in the US) sweeteners ” ) .
examples: This diner serves ketchup in red bottles, and mustard in yellow ones.

definitions.definition: Such a sauce more generally (not necessarily based on tomatoes, but with mushrooms, fish, etc.). This is the older meaning.

main_definition: ( uncountable , chiefly US , Canada , UK ) Ellipsis of tomato ketchup ( “ a tomato - vinegar -based sauce , sometimes containing spices , onion or garlic , and (especially in the US) sweeteners ” ) .
secondary_definitions: ( countable , now rare ) Such a sauce more generally (not necessarily based on tomatoes, but with mushrooms, fish, etc.). This is the older meaning.
